name: Procrastination Canyon
description:
Introduction

Photos show the canyon after extensive rain.

Approach

A swim is required to access the canyon. After this, the short walk follows a fire trail towards the base of the falls. Take a right turn up onto a ridge which continues the top of the falls. Prepare to fight with stinging nettle and wait-a-while.

Descent

The main event looks possible to be abseiled in 3 pitches with a 60m rope. The water level displayed in the thumbnail was after a substaintial overnight rain and would be atypical. Not known if descended yet.

Exit
